(387, 1, '2014-11-26 09:19:39', '2014-11-25 22:19:39', 'Car loans can be confusing when there are some car dealers and makers offering ‘zero percent interest’ car loans. While this sounds tempting, the best loan doesn’t always mean the lowest rate and additional fees are usually involved.\r\n\r\nFinding the best car loan requires research. For example, when taking a manufacturer’s ‘zero per cent’ interest car loan, you may be foregoing the opportunity to negotiate a better price on the purchase of the new car, making that car loan very expensive in the long run.\r\n\r\nMost car loans are for a fixed period ranging from three to five years, and the repayment terms are at fixed weekly, fortnightly or monthly costs.\r\n\r\n[button color="blue" title="Enquire Now" url=""]\r\n<h6>This website only contains general information. It does not contain financial advice, and does not take into account your objectives, circumstances, or needs.\r\nYou should obtain your own financial, taxation and legal advice before making any decision. Terms, conditions, and fees may apply, along with credit assessment criteria for loan products.\r\nMembers and representatives of the ParkTrent group may receive commissions in relation to the services they provide to you, or on your behalf.\r\nPark Trent Properties Group Pty Ltd ABN 89 101 491 507 Easy Plan Financial Services Pty Ltd ABN 62 087 763 193 Australian Credit Licence 387430, Authorised Representative Number 270479 of Millennium3 Financial Services Pty Ltd AFSL Number 244252</h6>', 'Car Loans', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '271-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-26 09:19:39', '2014-11-25 22:19:39', '', 271, 'http://easyplan.com.au/271-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(388, 1, '2014-11-26 09:20:50', '2014-11-25 22:20:50', 'Buying a home can be beyond reach for many potential home buyers.\r\n\r\nThis is where EasyPlan Financial Services are invaluable. Our team can help you secure a bridging loan to assist you with your first or next property purchase.\r\n<h3>How A Bridging Home Loan Works</h3>\r\nA bridging loan literally ‘bridges’ your financial needs between the time you need to settle on a home purchase and the time your funds are available from the sale of your property. The sale of property can be an investment property or an existing home.\r\n<h3>Bridging Loan Requirements</h3>\r\nYou will need to demonstrate that funds are forthcoming from one of the sources mentioned above.\r\n\r\nYou will also need to have savings for the difference in sales proceeds and the buying costs of the new property, or be qualified to secure additional loan funds to bridge the gap between sale and purchase.\r\n\r\nA bridging loan can be a complex transaction involving multiple parties and multiple sets of documents. The timing is critical for the bridge loan to be available. This is where a trusted firm such as EasyPlan Financial Services will be able to provide you with the peace of mind necessary in what would otherwise be a potentially stressful transaction.\r\n\r\n[button color="blue" title="Enquire Now" url=""]\r\n<h6>This website only contains general information. It does not contain financial advice, and does not take into account your objectives, circumstances, or needs.\r\nYou should obtain your own financial, taxation and legal advice before making any decision. Terms, conditions, and fees may apply, along with credit assessment criteria for loan products.\r\nMembers and representatives of the ParkTrent group may receive commissions in relation to the services they provide to you, or on your behalf.\r\nPark Trent Properties Group Pty Ltd ABN 89 101 491 507 Easy Plan Financial Services Pty Ltd ABN 62 087 763 193 Australian Credit Licence 387430, Authorised Representative Number 270479 of Millennium3 Financial Services Pty Ltd AFSL Number 244252</h6>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Bridging Loans', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '263-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-26 09:20:50', '2014-11-25 22:20:50', '', 263, 'http://easyplan.com.au/263-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(389, 1, '2014-11-26 09:21:14', '2014-11-25 22:21:14', 'EasyPlan offers property investors a rigorous system for assessing and qualifying an applicant for loan requirements.\r\n\r\nWith our experienced EasyPlan Financial team, you can be assured you will receive the best property investment loan for your needs.\r\n<h3>What is required?</h3>\r\nA property investor has advantages over a home owner as they are generally able to claim the costs of borrowing and all other costs associated with owning the investment property against their income. This also includes a deprecation allowance which may be available to the investor. As a borrower, an investor can also include up to 80 per cent of the net rental income in their loan serviceability calculation. This offers the property investor a higher borrowing capacity compared home owners.\r\n<h3>Investment loan checklist</h3>\r\nTo qualify for a loan on an investment property through our EasyPlan financial services, you must be able to demonstrate that you have either:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A history of savings to cover a deposit, or</li>\r\n	<li>Equity in an existing property such as your home or other investment property</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>The costs checklist:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Stamp duty on land transfer, which varies from state to state</li>\r\n	<li>Legal fees</li>\r\n	<li>Lender fees such as stamp duty associated with the mortgage, including mortgage transfer fees and application fees (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Pest and building reports</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Cash flow budget</h3>\r\nOur EasyPlan service includes a detailed personal budget that takes into account ongoing costs, as well as transaction costs, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mortgage repayment and a 1.5-2% buffer against interest rate rises</li>\r\n	<li>Building and landlord insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Council rates, water rates and any other fees</li>\r\n	<li>Property management fees to manage the rental term of a property.  These fees will range from 5% to 8% (plus GST)</li>\r\n	<li>Body corporate and strata fees if the property is an apartment or unit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLike all loans, you may be required to give additional items such as previous 2 years'' tax returns to satisfy the lender’s requirements.\r\n\r\n[button color="blue" title="Enquire Now" url=""]\r\n<h6>This website only contains general information. It does not contain financial advice, and does not take into account your objectives, circumstances, or needs.\r\nYou should obtain your own financial, taxation and legal advice before making any decision. Terms, conditions, and fees may apply, along with credit assessment criteria for loan products.\r\nMembers and representatives of the ParkTrent group may receive commissions in relation to the services they provide to you, or on your behalf.\r\nPark Trent Properties Group Pty Ltd ABN 89 101 491 507 Easy Plan Financial Services Pty Ltd ABN 62 087 763 193 Australian Credit Licence 387430, Authorised Representative Number 270479 of Millennium3 Financial Services Pty Ltd AFSL Number 244252</h6>', 'Property Investment Loans', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '267-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-26 09:21:14', '2014-11-25 22:21:14', '', 267, 'http://easyplan.com.au/267-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(390, 1, '2014-11-26 09:24:18', '2014-11-25 22:24:18', 'A credit card can be convenient and efficient, or it can be stressful and harmful to your credit rating.\r\n\r\nIf you''re thinking about buying a house or a car, your personal finances and your credit profile are critical. At EasyPlan Financial Services, we can help you carefully choose an affordable credit card that meets your needs.\r\n<h3><strong>The best credit card rate</strong></h3>\r\nThe best credit card for you may not be the card with the lowest interest rate. For example, if you are using your credit card wisely and pay the full amount each month, you don’t need to worry about the interest rate. Most people have at least one credit card and another line of credit such as a car loan or mortgage.\r\n<h3>Managing payments</h3>\r\nThe credit card is a powerful tool for managing your payments, too. Paying utility bills has never been easier but here again, the interest rate on the card can be punishingly high (over 20% in some cases) if the card is used unwisely.\r\n\r\nThe free period does not apply when you take a cash advance on a credit card, which can be one of the most expensive ways of accessing credit.\r\n\r\nThe best credit card rates for people who want to buy items and pay them off over time (for example, buying a holiday online) would be a card which offers a very low interest rate but not necessarily interest free days.\r\n\r\nOur EasyPlan experts can help you the find the best credit card rates and deals in Australia for your individual needs.\r\n\r\n[button color="blue" title="Enquire Now" url=""]\r\n<h6>This website only contains general information. It does not contain financial advice, and does not take into account your objectives, circumstances, or needs.\r\nYou should obtain your own financial, taxation and legal advice before making any decision. Terms, conditions, and fees may apply, along with credit assessment criteria for loan products.\r\nMembers and representatives of the ParkTrent group may receive commissions in relation to the services they provide to you, or on your behalf.\r\nPark Trent Properties Group Pty Ltd ABN 89 101 491 507 Easy Plan Financial Services Pty Ltd ABN 62 087 763 193 Australian Credit Licence 387430, Authorised Representative Number 270479 of Millennium3 Financial Services Pty Ltd AFSL Number 244252</h6>', 'Credit Cards', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '289-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-26 09:24:18', '2014-11-25 22:24:18', '', 289, 'http://easyplan.com.au/289-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
